UMkhonto Wesizwe Military Veterans Association spokesperson Carl Niehaus is appearing at the Escourt Magistrate Court on Thursday. He's facing criminal charges for violating COVID-19 regulations. eNCA reporter Lethiwe Mdluli has more on this story. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Suspended ANC member Carl Niehaus says the law is being abused. He was back in the Estcourt magistrate's court on Thursday, facing charges for breaking lockdown rules. READ: Carl Niehaus dismissed from the ANC Niehaus was arrested last year after rallying supporters outside the Estcourt prison where former President Jacob Zuma was imprisoned. Niehaus says the only reason he is being charged, is because of his support to Zuma. WATCH | ANC slams Carl Niehaus The case will continue on Friday. More witnesses are expected to take the stand.